definition.value: An organosulfur compound that has structure: R-C=N(OH)SH where R is any aryl, heteroaryl, or alkyl group.
A 2-hydroxy carboxylate that results from the removal of a proton from the carboxylic acid group of 3-phenyllactic acid.

A steroid acid resulting from the oxidation of one of the terminal methyl groups of cholesterol to the corresponding aldehyde.
An acyl fluoride with phenylmethanesulfonyl as the acyl group.
